#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin:1
msgid ""
"Mixin that allows an instance to organize the processing     of PDF "
"files. This is done in the constructor using the     "
":meth:`pathfile_to_sheets <.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets>`     and "
":meth:`path_to_sheets <.DirFilePDFMixin.path_to_sheets>` methods     by "
"storing the results in the :attr:`sheets <.DirFilePDFMixin.sheets>`     "
"property."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin:3
msgid ""
"The path to consider is indicated through the \"source\"     argument "
"defined in the constructor. If the path is a PDF     file it will be "
"processed, however if it is a directory     it will be recursively "
"traversed processing all the PDF     files it finds."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin:5
msgid ""
"In addition, it defines the :attr:`metadata <.DirFilePDFMixin.metadata>`"
"     property to store information related to the processed files and the"
"     :attr:`verbose <.DirFilePDFMixin.verbose>` property that determines"
"     if the process and results is printed on the screen. The latter is"
"     definable through the constructor as a \"verbose\" argument and only"
"     supports boolean value."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin:7
msgid "It is a subclass of :class:`ProcessorPDFMixin <.ProcessorPDFMixin>`."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.metadata:1
msgid ""
"Property that stores in a dictionary the metadata of the         "
"processed documents ('files' key), the library used to process         it"
" ('processor' key) and the initialization times ('ini' key)."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.path_to_sheets:1
msgid ""
"Method receives a path that it searches for PDF files to apply method"
"         :meth:`pathfile_to_sheets <.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets>`"
" to each one.         The result is returned in a single list of sheets."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.path_to_sheets:3
msgid ""
"It applies recursion to go deeper into the directories using the 'depth' "
"and         'max_depth' parameters. The 'depth' parameter indicates the "
"depth in relation         to the first call, it also implements "
"indentation on screen printing. The 'max_depth'         parameter "
"determines the maximum depth in which to search for PDF files."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.path_to_sheets:5
#: serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets:10
msgid ""
"Its manual use is not recommended but it is feasible, the method         "
"is intended to be activated from the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets:1
msgid ""
"Method takes a valid path for a PDF file, uses a PDF processor,         "
"and then returns a list with the sheets in text string."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets:3
msgid ""
"If a object is configured as verbose, that is to say property  "
":attr:`verbose <.DirFilePDFMixin.verbose>` is true,         it will print"
" on the screen the process and details of the         extraction result. "
"By default it will not print anything on screen."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets:6
msgid ""
"This method internally records metadata from file processing in         "
"the :attr:`metadata <.DirFilePDFMixin.metadata>` property with         "
"the \"files\" key."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.pathfile_to_sheets:8
msgid ""
"The 'depth' argument is for the indentation of the screen print         "
"in case it is in verbose mode."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.sheets:1
msgid ""
"Property to store the list of sheets or pages in text         chain of "
"the processed PDF files."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.DirFilePDFMixin.verbose:1
msgid ""
"Property that defines whether the instance prints its         progress or"
" results on the screen. This property is only         definable in the "
"constructor of the class in the \"verbose\"         argument with a "
"boolean value."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin:1
msgid ""
"Mixin that allows an instance the ability to process     PDF files with "
"certain libraries. In the constructor,     the processor to be used is "
"defined with the argument     of the same name, binding the "
":attr:`process_pdf     <.ProcesosrPDFMixin.process_pdf>` property to the"
"     method related to it."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin:3
msgid "PDF processor availables:"
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin:5
msgid ""
"`pdftotext <https://github.com/jalan/pdftotext>`_         (0.1.0 release)"
" with :meth:`pdftotext_processor         "
"<.ProcessorPDFMixin.processor_pdftotext>`"
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin.process_pdf:1
msgid ""
"Property that calls the method corresponding to the PDF file         "
"processor configured in the instance initialization."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin.processor_name:1
msgid ""
"Property containing the name of the PDF processor used         in the "
"instance."
msgstr ""

#: of serveliza.mixins.pdf.ProcessorPDFMixin.processor_pdftotext:1
msgid ""
"Method to use `pdftotext <https://github.com/jalan/pdftotext>`_         "
"in a file specified in the argument as a path."
msgstr ""

